Does ABC have a formalized, centralized structure? There is a lot of formalization and centralization at ABC Corp. The degree of standardization and recording of procedures and processes inside an organization is referred to as formalization. In ABC Corp., every employee has a well defined and established job description, and the firm has thoroughly documented processes. Given that there is a defined set of policies and procedures that workers are required to follow, this suggests that the organization has a high degree of formalization. The degree to which decision-making power is concentrated at the highest levels of an organization is referred to as centralization. In ABC Corp., there is a CEO to whom everyone reports via a select number of managers, and low-level workers are not given a lot of power to make decisions. As decision-making authority is centralized at the highest levels of the organization, this suggests that the corporation has a high degree of centralization. 